Yae Lidia!!

Buy squeeky (when squeezed) artichokes -- no rubbery stems

minced garlic in olive oil
add minced shallot and a pinch of salt
a pinch of red pepper

add a bit of the water from the boil

move the vegies to the side and add cubed potatos
add Diced leakes
add bay leaves

peel outter leaves of Artichoke
cut the tops off the artichoke
cut in half and pearing knife out the choke and beard

Slice artichokes and add to water bowl that has sliced lemons.

add the hot water to the veggies, salt

30 minutes on simmer fully covered

serve rustic hitting it olive oil, fromagio, red pepper.
